The Nigerian Army says soldiers in military uniform threatening to rape women in Delta State have been arrested. The threat video preceded the killing of a soldier in Warri, Delta State, during a clash. The Nigerian Army in a tweet on its official Twitter handle on Friday said the soldiers were arrested on 3rd April, 2020 at 9 Brigade, Ikeja Military Cantonment, Lagos. The statement said investigation has  commenced into the matter and the outcome will be made public. “Soldiers in a viral video using uncouth  and uncivilized language purportedly threatening to molest  women in Warri Delta State were arrested at 9 Brigade Ikeja Military Cantonment Lagos State today 3 April 2020 and further investigation is ongoing. “The general public should be assured that the investigations will be swift and fair in accordance with applicable military laws. “The outcome of th investigations will determine the most appropriate disciplinary measures that can be taken in the circumstances 2/3. “The Nigerian Army wishes to reiterate that it would not tolerate any form of irresponsibility and indiscipline on the part of any of its personnel”, it said.